NAME
    mktemp - create a temporary file or directory

SYNOPSIS
    mktemp [options] [template]

DESCRIPTION
    Creates a unique temporary file or directory and prints
    its name. The template must contain at least 3 X's which
    are replaced with random characters.

OPTIONS
    -d              Create directory instead of file
    -u              Dry run (print name without creating)
    -q              Quiet (suppress error messages)
    -p <dir>        Create in directory (default: /tmp)
    -t              Use template relative to prefix dir
    --suffix=<suf>  Append suffix after X substitution

TEMPLATE
    Default template is tmp.XXXXXXXXXX
    X's are replaced with random alphanumeric characters.
    At least 3 consecutive X's required.

EXAMPLES
    mktemp
        /tmp/tmp.A7xK3mPqR2

    mktemp -d
        /tmp/tmp.B9yL4nQsT1 (directory)

    mktemp myapp.XXXX
        /tmp/myapp.Z5wM

    mktemp -p /home/user cache.XXX
        /home/user/cache.K8n

    mktemp --suffix=.json data.XXXX
        /tmp/data.P3rQ.json

    mktemp -u test.XXX
        Print name only, don't create

EXIT STATUS
    0       Success
    1       Error (couldn't create file/directory)

SEE ALSO
    touch, mkdir, rm
